abstract: >
  The Agent Registry (AREG) is a Schema Commons open standard defining a
  machine-readable registry entry format and REST API for publishing, discovering,
  and resolving AAIF-format AI agent definitions. A registry entry records the
  agent's stable identity, version, publisher, resolution URL, capability summary,
  and optional signing information. AREG is the discovery layer of the Schema
  Commons agent stack, complementing SC-006 AAIF (agent definition portability)
  and SC-014 ACPM (capability profiles).
